Diana & Marvin is a duets album by American soul musicians Diana Ross and
Marvin Gaye, released October 26, 1973 on Motown. Recording sessions for the
album took place in 1972 and 1973 at Motown Recording Studios in Hollywood,
California. Featuring vocal collaborations by Gaye and Ross, widely recognized
at the time as two of the top soul and pop performers, respectively
